    "href": "AIP/quality-rules/7944",
    "critical": false,
    "severity": 10,
    "maxWeight": 8,
    "associatedValueName": "Response For Class",
    "description": "Avoid High Response for a Class (RFC > X)\nRFC is the total number of local methods and remote methods called by methods in the Class.\nThe threshold is a parameter and can be changed at will.\n\nFor Power Builder, Classes designates PB Applications, Datastores, Menus, Userobjects and Windows.",
    "output": "This report lists all Classes with High Response for a Class\nIt provides the following information:\nClass full name, RFC",
    "rationale": "If a large number of methods can be invoked in response to a message, the testing and debugging of the Class becomes more complicated since it requires a greater level of understanding required on the part of the tester.",
    "reference": "A Metrics Suite for Object Oriented Design\nChidamber, S.R. and C.F. Kemerer\nIEEE Transactions on Software Engineering, 1994",
    "remediation": "Reduce the number of local methods and remote methods called by methods in the Class",
    "total": "Number of classes",
    "alternativeName": "Ensure you have a number of local methods and remote methods called by methods in the Class below a predefined threshold",
